gov.usgs.anss.util

Class ConnectionStatus

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.util.ConnectionStatus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StatusInfo, java.lang.Comparable

    public class ConnectionStatus
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable, StatusInfo
    The ConnectionStatus contains one group of information from the UDP channel system plus data derived for successive updates of this data. Basiccally it is the IP addresses and ports involved and whether there was a connect or disconnect.

      • update

        public void update(java.lang.Object o)
        Update a existing channel with information from a new packet. The input is a generic object because the UDP software is generalized to handle many types of data for distribution. Various statistics are computed from the existing data and the data in the new object - whether a "other stream" is working, total bytes received, last times,etc.
        Specified by:
        update in interface StatusInfo
        Parameters:
        o - An object which must downcast to a ConnectionStatus
